cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|   Hi Everyone and welcome to today's Precision Club session, in which we'll be starting to have a look at what to do when opponents interfere during our Asking Bid Sequence.

We've touched on a few aspects of this over the weeks when we've been covering the Asking Bids, but now it's time to learn systematically how we deal with interference.

This is all too frequent an occurrence and you have to be prepared for it.

If you really get your act together with partner you can frequently turn ill-advised interference to your advantage.

In general, though, the aim is simply to conserve and reclaim as much bidding space as possible.

This is not an easy topic even if you are already reasonably comfortable with the Asking Bids that we've covered over the last couple of months, because most of the concepts will be new, so be prepared for a rough ride.

Some of the concepts that we'll be covering today, though, can be very useful, whatever system you play.

If you have not already done so, please have a look at the notes I have prepared on Precision Club bidding.

You can find these on: ^*h http://bbo.pigpen.org.uk ^*n The notes on Interference during Asking Bid sequences can be found at ^*h http://bbo.pigpen.org.uk/AskingInterference.php ^*n. 

If you are new to Asking Bids then there's no way you're going to absorb everything we cover tonight, so please do visit the site and read through the Asking Bid section at your leisure.

Ok, let's get started|
