cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|   If you start playing Precision regularly, you will find that opponents (especially good ones) tend to interfere a fair amount, especially during  1@C  sequences.

Many Precision pairs are not prepared for this and consequently allow their auction to be disrupted to a considerable extent or even have to completely "abandon" their sequences.

It is my intention that you should ^*b NOT ^*N fall into this category.   Clearly if the bidding starts something like 1@C - (5@S), there isn't going to be a whole lot of space for you to do much.

But even so, the methods I'm going to show you over the next few weeks will at least allow you a degree of control and the option of Asking further.|
