cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Intervention immediately over an ASKING BID.

We're now going to introduce you to a couple of acronyms, (which you may already know): 

DOPI & ROPI.   DOPI stands for   Double Zero Pass One    and   ROPI  stands for   Redouble Zero Pass One.

What we are using here isn't quite  DOPI  &  ROPI,  but very close (more like  D1P2  &  R1P2).

The point is that we can now use ^*b Double ^*n and/or ^*b Pass ^*n as responses to the Asking Bid.  So:

^c^*bDouble^*n / ^*bRedouble^*n ^h shows the   1 step   response
^c^*bPass^*n                    ^h shows the   2 step   response   (hence D1P2 and R1P2) 
^c^*nthe next bid up^*n           ^h shows the   3 step   response,  etc

DOPI and ROPI are not a concept confined to Precision and many people who use Blackwood also use DOPI & ROPI (or their cousins DOPE and ROPE [odd/even])

DOPI and ROPI are very useful with Asking Bids, as you can save up to ^*b 2 steps ^*n in your response and reclaim some space.  For example:
^c@2
1@c  -  1@H  -  1NT(Beta)  -  (2@D)       now 
^d@2
Double ^fshows ^h0-2  ^ictrls,
Pass ^fshows   ^h3    ^ictrls 
2@H ^fshows    ^h4    ^ictrls, etc, and you've reclaimed  ALL  of the space lost due to the intervention.
^b@2|
